
1. Generar hash sha512 para usar en /etc/shadow

$ python -c "import crypt; print crypt.crypt('redhat')"
$6$r.vbAZmgtX2ReFkW$YdP0MjO6Yhm/tXqcLuHdznM8dHyEB8gwXU0evtSx2M9AVn9qcPgl.mvbpnDkr0ypFNlTLT4uqkmf0RsEWV4ms0

2. Generar hash sha512 de una cadena

$ echo -n "redhat" | openssl dgst -sha512
(stdin)= f98e699a5496ad051140be0e7834f31fae150733173bef925b6cf6df0a793118fb3e07b82ccbad3c07dc8dd295d1b7a2fe7b5d037986195258edc1356bd25d8e



